content.text:
The issue was that in `CardBrowser.kt`, when in multi-select mode, tapping a card row (which triggers `setOnItemClickListener`) was calling `viewModel.selectRowAtPosition(position)`. This method in `CardBrowserViewModel` only *adds* the card to the selection set, it does not toggle it. As a result, tapping an already selected card would not unselect it.

I fixed this by changing the call to `viewModel.toggleRowSelectionAtPosition(position)`, which correctly handles both selecting and unselecting cards.

I verified the fix by creating a reproduction test case `CardBrowserSelectionTest.kt` which simulated the issue (entering multi-select, selecting a second card, then trying to unselect the first card). The test failed before the fix and passed after the fix. I also ran existing tests in `CardBrowserTest` to ensure no regressions.

I have removed the temporary test file to keep the codebase clean.

**Files Modified:**
- `AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/anki/CardBrowser.kt`: Changed `viewModel.selectRowAtPosition(position)` to `viewModel.toggleRowSelectionAtPosition(position)` inside `setOnItemClickListener`.

```kotlin
// AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/anki/CardBrowser.kt

// ...
        cardsListView.setOnItemClickListener { _: AdapterView<*>?, view: View?, position: Int, _: Long ->
            if (isInMultiSelectMode) {
                // click on whole cell triggers select
                val cb = view!!.findViewById<CheckBox>(R.id.card_checkbox)
                cb.toggle()
                viewModel.toggleRowSelectionAtPosition(position) // Changed from selectRowAtPosition
            } else {
// ...
```

